This paper is about using deep neural networks for age and gender classification, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of patches and feature extraction, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed method on two databases, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
